@NODE Introduction "Introduction"

@{b}Introduction@{ub}

You have lots of images in your software collection and you want to maintain
them in a comfortable, GUI-based way? Then RTN is the tool you were always
waiting for!

RTN reads images in various file-formats specified by a list (LST-file), scales
the pictures (with correct aspect) to thumbnails and merges them to a 
Contents-Image (TOC-file). In addition file-name and resolution is printed to
the image. ThumbNail is highly configurable, but ready to use.
@ENDNODE

@NODE Features "Features"

@{b}Features@{ub}

   +  Easy to use graphical user interface (MUI)
   +  Click on thumbnail to display fullscale picture
   +  Online help
   +  Configuration via Workbench-Tooltypes
   +  Two sophisticated scaling algorithms

   +  Various supported file-formats:
         +  IFF (any !)
         +  BMP
         +  JPEG
         +  PGM
         +  PPM
         +  QRT
         +  SUNRASTER
         +  XIPAINT
         +  OS 3.0 datatypes!
            You can find some interesting on Aminet, for ex.
               -> GIF
               -> TIF
               -> PCX
               -> Postscript
               -> Targa
               -> XBitmap
@ENDNODE

@NODE System-Requirements "System-Requirements"

@{b}System-Requirements@{ub}

   +  Amiga equipped with 68020, 68881 or better running OS 2.0, for online-help
      and datatypes OS 3.0 required.

   +  Magic User Interface (MUI)

   +  Macrosystem Retina Gfx-Board

   +  RetinaDisplay

   +  retina.library

   +  multipic.library

   +  retinaemu.library

   +  ixemul.library (if you still miss it, have a look at aminet/dev/gcc),

   +  some RAM (or even more ?).


   If you run low on memory (who doesn't?) try VMM, a virtual memory manager
   by Martin Apel, available on Aminet.
@ENDNODE

